      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CURADH (2) has been in good form of late and went well again when off a back row draw last time at Gloucester Park, finishing second and 5.5 metres from the winner. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw and won his lone attempt at this circuit and distance so he is a major player. HOLY HECKA NZ (4) turned in a much better run at his latest appearance, finishing second at Gloucester Park. Has won when third-up before so could go one better. RAKERO RAIDER NZ (11) has had little luck in two outings at Gloucester Park since a spell, held up fresh and racing wide last time. Fitter for those hitouts and owns a decent record at this circuit and distance. YAWOMA (1) led from wider to win in the city last start so is aided by the ace draw.",
